s-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pmiguet/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f427129b135d68aef8e6ae1193356900ab6835e3adf19f4ce31bac4b1d0b4ded?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f427129b135d68aef8e6ae1193356900ab6835e3adf19f4ce31bac4b1d0b4ded?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pmiguet/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">pmiguet</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">octobre 8, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I really love this plugin, it (almost) ticks all the boxes and I really don\'t understand why WP does not integrate a feature like this from the start.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the major things that I am missing though is the template import/export feature. I setup a really nice page on one site and wanted to use it somewhere else, and it was a bit tedious to copy all the settings. Here and there a few minor improvements, i.e. explaining properly what a setting does. Sometimes I changed something and didn\'t see any change. So it needs a bit of experimenting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other than that, really loving this and will be using this for the foreseeable future. I also wouldn\'t mind if it had a one-off fee to pay (as long as it\'s not subscription based).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-ti